Serious precautions should therefore be taken to protect the population, especially health workers, social workers, their relatives, colleagues and even others who are in contact with patients or infected.
The first line of defense in the fight to reduce the risk of infection is wearing facial masks; and surgical masks, and N95-class respirators (series No. 1860s) help control the spread of viruses.
Surgical masks do not allow microcaples of liquid from potentially infected to fly in the air and settle on the surfaces from which they can be transmitted to others.
