On March 19, 2020, the Coalition for Epidemic Preparedness Innovation (CEPI), France, announced that $4.9 million had been invested in the COVID-19 vaccine consortium, with the participation of the Pasteur Institute, Themis Bioscience (Vienna, Austria) and the University of Pittsburgh.
